parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floor, resulting in total brake failure, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
continuous brake failure
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake failure after driving at low speeds
brake failure after repeated repair attempts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the parking brake can cause the parking brake to lock, leading to overheating, transmission failure, and engine failure, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The parking brake locks
the parking brake drum overheats
the transmission fails
the engine fails
the parking brake is difficult to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Failure due to Brake Problems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission failure caused by brake problems can result in loss of gears, including overdrive and reverse, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The transmission fails
the transmission overheats
the transmission loses gears
the transmission has no overdrive or reverse gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Failure due to Brake Problems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure caused by brake problems can result in engine failure, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine fails
the engine overheats
the engine has undue strain on the drivetrain.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction to the driver and passengers, potentially leading to accidents or heat-related health issues.
symptoms: The air conditioning is not blowing cold air
the air conditioning is not working
the reservoir cap has failed
the air conditioning system is leaking refrigerant.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front air suspension can cause uneven ride height, reduced handling, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle sags or leans to one side
the air suspension warning light is illuminated
the vehicle has a rough or bouncy ride
the vehicle has uneven tire wear
the vehicle has reduced ground clearance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sway bar brackets can cause reduced handling and stability, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle has uneven tire wear
the vehicle has reduced handling and stability
the vehicle has a loud clunking or rattling noise
the vehicle has a loose or broken sway bar bracket.
